&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;The Ground &amp;amp; Control Services (GCS) team is seeking a thoughtful and technically strong Engineering Manager to lead the group responsible for building the autonomous systems that control and monitor BlackSky’s satellite constellation. This team owns high‑speed tasking, ground and space telemetry, health monitoring, and low‑latency communication with ground stations worldwide. As the GCS Manager, you will guide the engineers who design, build, and operate software that bridges hardware‑level interfaces with cloud‑deployed microservices—software that keeps our satellites healthy, safe, and responsive 24/7.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;In this role, you’ll provide technical direction, build healthy engineering processes, and cultivate a culture of curiosity, safety, and ownership. You will partner with mission operations, spacecraft engineering, product teams, and program leadership to ensure the team consistently meets both commercial production goals and program‑driven requirements. This includes balancing long‑term reliability with rapid iteration, supporting operational readiness for live constellation needs, and delivering capabilities aligned with customer commitments and program milestones.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;You’ll help your team reason about complex autonomous systems where reliability matters as much as performance, and you’ll play a key part in scaling our constellation as we grow. Success in this role means enabling your team to deliver high-quality, dependable software; ensuring operational excellence; communicating effectively across disciplines; and supporting engineers in developing their careers while fostering a collaborative, mission-focused environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;This role reports to the Director, Ground Apps and Services and is strongly preferred to be in the Seattle, WA area.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Who you are:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-s

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marketing Content Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;BlackSky BlackSky is a real-time intelligence company. We own and operate the world&#39;s most advanced space-based intelligence platform and provide customers satellite imagery, automated analytics and high-frequency monitoring of strategic locations, economic assets and events from around the globe. BlackSky is trusted by the most demanding allied military and intelligence organizations and commercial companies to deliver foresight into critical matters that affect national security and the economy. BlackSky&#39;s data enables governments and businesses to see, understand and anticipate change as it happens, giving them the ultimate strategic advantage so they can act quickly. Our global team works with cutting-edge technology to make a difference around the world and prides itself on being people-first, customer-focused and fun.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BlackSky is seeking a hands-on Marketing Content Specialist to bring marketing strategies and messages to life across various, primarily digital, channels. In this role, you will create high-quality, compelling content across multiple platforms, including our website, social media, email, blog, customer presentations and more. The ideal candidate will have a strong understanding of content and social media marketing, excellent writing and multimedia skills and a bias for action. To be successful, you must be detail-oriented and organized, while taking proactively taking ownership of projects and assignments. This hybrid position is based in Seattle, Washington, and be responsible for capturing visual content in BlackSky’s offices and reports to the Senior Director, Marketing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement content marketing plans that align with the overall marketing goals and priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create engaging and informative written content for blogs, social media posts, email campaigns, newsletters and website copy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage BlackSky social media channels, to include calendaring and planning, content creation and engagement management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate photo and video shoots to capture new content for promotion, in addition to capturing regular photo and video yourself.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze content performance using analytics tools to track engagement and suggest improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the design team to ensure content is visually appealing and aligned with brand guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create graphics and visuals in alignment with brand guidelines for use across digital channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in developing editorial calendars and campaign timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Edit and proofread content to ensure accuracy, clarity, and consistency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up-to-date with industry trends, content marketing best practices and competitor digital content strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other job-related duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Marketing, Journalism, English, or Business (or equivalent experience in lieu of a degree).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 4 years of experience in content marketing, corporate marketing or digital marketing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience managing corporate social media accounts for B2B or B2G.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding communication skills with the capacity to explain and translate complex technology concepts into simple and intuitive narrative.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Adobe Creative Suite, particularly for the purposes of photo editing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional attention to detail, even when managing multiple deadlines.&lt;/

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mechanical Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BlackSky is a real-time intelligence company. We own and operate the world&#39;s most advanced space-based intelligence platform and provide customers satellite imagery, automated analytics and high-frequency monitoring of strategic locations, economic assets, and events from around the globe. BlackSky is trusted by the most demanding allied military and intelligence organizations and commercial companies to deliver foresight into critical matters that affect national security and the economy. BlackSky&#39;s data enables governments and businesses to see, understand and anticipate change as it happens, giving them the ultimate strategic advantage so they can act quickly. Our global team works with cutting-edge technology to make a difference around the world and prides itself on being people-first, customer-focused and fun.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Mechanical Engineer at BlackSky you will support the full program lifecycle of our satellite systems and components, from concept to production.&amp;nbsp; You will be involved in the development, design, test, and production of our satellite systems, components, and supporting hardware. You will develop initial concepts of satellite structures, system layouts, and support equipment based on requirements and objectives, then apply BlackSky best practices, mentorship from senior engineers, and your own skills and intuition to fully mature those concepts. &amp;nbsp;You will create CAD models, select materials, generate and maintain manufacturing documentation, and support production.&amp;nbsp; You will interact with flight, prototype, and ground support hardware. &amp;nbsp;You will do all this as part of a highly skilled multi-functional technical team focused on producing state-of-the-art satellites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position reports to the Director, Mechanical Engineering and is a hybrid role based out of our Tukwila, WA office.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design spacecraft mechanical structures, assemblies, and components with CAD software (Creo)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate and maintain engineering and manufacturing documentation such as part drawings, assembly drawings, and bills of materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document design and analysis data in technical reports, presentations, and manufacturing systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support manufacturing and production teams by providing design intent, resolving build issues, reviewing nonconformance reports, and implementing corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop tooling, fixtures, and ground support equipment as needed to support integration and test activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply engineering judgment to make informed decisions when data is incomplete, balancing performance, manufacturability, reliability, and schedule.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work within a multidisciplinary team to deliver space vehicle designs, production plans, and test strategies that support program cost, schedule, and quality goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other responsibilities as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor of Science degree in Mechanical Engineering, Aerospace Engineering, or a similar engineering discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least (3) three years of professional experience in a mechanical engineering role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using CAD software to develop part and assembly models, and manufacturing drawings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable experience maturing designs from initial concepts to detailed manufacturing drawings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of the ANSI Y14.5 dimensioning and tolerancing specification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mechanical Engineer – Wire Harness&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
